    <text id="B0185T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Sallie Myers submits a reference for an Esther Smith, who has worked for Myers
                    for 15 months. Smith had submitted a complaint against her husband, Albert
                    Smith, who deserted her in 1863.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Officer of the Bureau Department</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-03-21">March 21st/68</date>
                        <name type="place">Near Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Kind Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>This woman came to you in trouble. Please hear her statement and give her the
                        <orig reg="advice">advise</orig> and information she asks. You can rely on
                    what she tells you. I have had her employed for the last fifteen months and <hi
                        rend="underline">know</hi> her to be an honest, truthful <add hand="h1"
                        place="inline">&amp;</add> virtuous woman.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully,</salute>
                    <signed>Sallie Myers</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">[Written in Jackson's hand] "Esther Smith (<abbr
                            expan="colored">c</abbr>) has 4 children by Albert Smith (<abbr
                            expan="colored">c</abbr>) who now lives at <unclear>Chilberth</unclear>
                        Ohio with a wife. Deserted Esther in 1863 <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> &amp; has
                        done nothing for her since. Now wants to claim two oldest children. <del
                            hand="h1"/> TPJ"</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
